1030
01:12:19,840 --> 01:12:21,680
Scare him off?

1031
01:12:29,120 --> 01:12:30,800
[Intercom Buzzes]

1032
01:12:34,240 --> 01:12:35,600
Yes?

1033
01:12:35,680 --> 01:12:38,960
Woman: A call for you from a man
who says he's an old friend

1034
01:12:39,040 --> 01:12:40,680
and wonders if you'll
recognize his voice.

1035
01:12:40,760 --> 01:12:43,800
Do you want the call that way,
or shall I insist upon his name?

1036
01:12:43,880 --> 01:12:45,200
Ok, I'll take it.

1037
01:12:45,280 --> 01:12:46,640
I'm putting you through.

1038
01:12:49,120 --> 01:12:50,200
Paul: Hello?

1039
01:12:50,280 --> 01:12:52,120
Is this Paul Kersey?

1040
01:12:52,200 --> 01:12:53,920
Yes. Who's this?

1041
01:12:54,000 --> 01:12:58,720
Mr. Kersey, you're under
police surveillance.

1042
01:12:58,800 --> 01:13:00,680
You're being watched.

1043
01:13:02,200 --> 01:13:04,280
[Dial Tone]

1044
01:13:09,120 --> 01:13:11,400
Scare him off. Ha!

1045
01:13:23,320 --> 01:13:25,920
Man: Papers! Papers!

1046
01:13:26,000 --> 01:13:29,120
Read all about the vigilante!

1047
01:13:29,200 --> 01:13:32,000
Get your papers here!

1048
01:13:32,080 --> 01:13:34,240
Read all about the vigilante!

1049
01:13:34,320 --> 01:13:36,320
How are you this evening, sir?

1050
01:13:36,400 --> 01:13:39,040
Papers! Papers!

1051
01:13:39,120 --> 01:13:41,480
Read all about the vigilante!

1052
01:13:56,720 --> 01:13:59,000
Police Officer:
All right, you. Get your hands up.

1053
01:13:59,080 --> 01:14:01,000
Come on.
Hands on the car. Come on.

1054
01:14:01,080 --> 01:14:02,360
Spread your legs.

1055
01:14:09,600 --> 01:14:11,640
OK. Turn around.

1056
01:14:11,720 --> 01:14:14,200
Let's see some identification.

1057
01:14:14,280 --> 01:14:17,080
[Indistinct Police Radio]

1058
01:14:19,400 --> 01:14:20,960
Where do you live?

1059
01:14:21,040 --> 01:14:22,520
33 Riverside.

1060
01:14:22,600 --> 01:14:24,920
OK, Mr. Kersey.
Sorry to have roughed you up so much.

1061
01:14:25,000 --> 01:14:26,520
We're looking for a guy

1062
01:14:26,600 --> 01:14:27,960
pretty close
to your description.

1063
01:14:28,040 --> 01:14:29,080
He's supposed to be armed,

1064
01:14:29,160 --> 01:14:30,960
and we couldn't take
any chances.

1065
01:14:31,040 --> 01:14:32,720
I hope you understand.

1066
01:14:32,800 --> 01:14:34,920
Look, if you want to
make a complaint,

1067
01:14:35,000 --> 01:14:36,280
I'll give you my number.

1068
01:14:36,360 --> 01:14:37,840
It's all right.
Nobody was hurt.

1069
01:14:37,920 --> 01:14:39,320
Police Officer:
OK. Thanks.

1070
01:14:39,400 --> 01:14:40,760
Good night,
Mr. Kersey.

1071
01:14:46,600 --> 01:14:48,280
OK?

1072
01:14:48,360 --> 01:14:49,880
Yeah.

1073
01:14:49,960 --> 01:14:51,320
OK.

1074
01:15:10,920 --> 01:15:13,800
Went in the building
about 10 minutes ago.

1075
01:15:13,880 --> 01:15:16,040
Went to D'Agostino's Market first.

1076
01:15:59,480 --> 01:16:02,280
[Indistinct Police Radio]

1077
01:16:13,400 --> 01:16:15,080
Let's check him, huh?

1078
01:16:15,160 --> 01:16:18,280
Go to that phone booth
on the corner, call his number.

1079
01:16:18,360 --> 01:16:19,560
He's up there.

1080
01:16:19,640 --> 01:16:21,480
Check him anyway.

1081
01:16:21,560 --> 01:16:24,360
[Mutters Indistinctly]

1082
01:17:07,520 --> 01:17:09,840
[Indistinct Police Radio]

1083
01:17:33,000 --> 01:17:35,160
Officer: Police!
I need the phone.

1084
01:17:35,240 --> 01:17:36,280
Come on!

1085
01:17:36,360 --> 01:17:37,560
Who is this guy?

1086
01:17:37,640 --> 01:17:39,160
Girl:
He must be crazy.

1087
01:17:39,240 --> 01:17:40,960
He said "police".
I didn't see a badge.

1088
01:17:44,040 --> 01:17:46,840
[Telephone Ringing]

1089
01:17:46,920 --> 01:17:49,520
I'll call as soon
as he gets off the phone.

1090
01:17:49,600 --> 01:17:50,520
Thanks, pal.

1091
01:17:50,600 --> 01:17:52,640
Yeah? Up yours!

1092
01:17:58,880 --> 01:18:01,680
No answer. He could be
in the shower or something.

1093
01:18:01,760 --> 01:18:02,800
Stay here.

1094
01:18:29,360 --> 01:18:31,920
[Indistinct Police Radio]

1095
01:18:56,200 --> 01:18:57,760
Good night, Mr. Kersey.

1096
01:18:57,840 --> 01:18:59,080
Good night.

1097
01:19:26,920 --> 01:19:29,440
I'm supposed to meet Paul Kersey.
Has he gone up yet?

1098
01:19:29,520 --> 01:19:31,520
Yes, sir. He went up
and came down.

1099
01:19:31,600 --> 01:19:32,880
Just walked out.

1100
01:19:53,000 --> 01:19:55,240
[Tires Squeal]

1101
01:20:01,960 --> 01:20:03,160
Where did you go?

1102
01:20:03,240 --> 01:20:05,080
He didn't show here, did he?

1103
01:20:05,160 --> 01:20:07,000
Can I ask a simple question?

1104
01:20:07,080 --> 01:20:08,760
Is this Paul Kersey the bird?

1105
01:20:10,280 --> 01:20:12,600
I ain't gonna ask
any more questions.

1106
01:20:12,680 --> 01:20:15,160
Go home, will you?
I don't need you.

1107
01:20:15,240 --> 01:20:16,240
Weird!

1108
01:20:24,840 --> 01:20:27,160
[Boat Horn Blows]

1109
01:20:44,040 --> 01:20:46,920
Come on down,
motherfucker.

1110
01:20:47,000 --> 01:20:48,560
We going to take you.

1111
01:20:48,640 --> 01:20:50,440
That's right, motherfucker,

1112
01:20:50,520 --> 01:20:53,320
and you can't
go back up, either.

1113
01:20:53,400 --> 01:20:56,200
[Muggers Laughing]

1114
01:21:00,240 --> 01:21:03,240
Come on down and bring us
the money, honey.

1115
01:21:03,320 --> 01:21:05,960
Second Mugger:
How much money you got, honey?

1116
01:21:06,040 --> 01:21:07,560
Ha ha ha ha!

1117
01:21:11,560 --> 01:21:12,520
What the fuck?

1118
01:21:13,960 --> 01:21:15,720
Fuck!

1119
01:21:28,280 --> 01:21:29,440
Ah!

1120
01:21:32,800 --> 01:21:35,560
[Siren]

1121
01:21:48,320 --> 01:21:50,360
Police Radio:
Units in the 2-6 precinct.

1122
01:21:50,440 --> 01:21:53,600
A 10-34, 1-2-5 Street
and the West Side Highway.

1123
01:22:56,000 --> 01:22:58,960
[Siren]

1124
01:23:05,280 --> 01:23:06,320
Paul: Hey!

1125
01:23:13,280 --> 01:23:14,400
Fill your hand.

1126
01:23:14,480 --> 01:23:16,240
Huh?

1127
01:23:19,840 --> 01:23:20,880
Draw.

1128
01:23:24,640 --> 01:23:27,640
[Siren]

1129
01:23:31,480 --> 01:23:34,240
[Crowd Yelling]

1130
01:23:34,320 --> 01:23:37,160
[Car Horn Honking]

1131
01:23:44,800 --> 01:23:47,560
[Siren]

1132
01:23:49,360 --> 01:23:52,200
[Indistinct Police Radio]

1133
01:24:02,320 --> 01:24:03,960
Where is he,
this patrolman?

1134
01:24:19,120 --> 01:24:20,160
You're Reilly?

1135
01:24:20,240 --> 01:24:21,280
Yes, sir.

1136
01:24:21,360 --> 01:24:22,400
I'm Ochoa.

1137
01:24:24,400 --> 01:24:26,560
You were the first man
on the scene?

1138
01:24:26,640 --> 01:24:27,520
Yes, sir.

1139
01:24:27,600 --> 01:24:28,640
[Sneezes]

1140
01:24:28,720 --> 01:24:30,040
God bless you, sir.

1141
01:24:30,120 --> 01:24:31,480
Never mind that.

1142
01:24:31,560 --> 01:24:34,680
They told me on the radio
you had to see me?

1143
01:24:34,760 --> 01:24:36,280
Paul Kersey.

1144
01:24:36,360 --> 01:24:39,800
You spoke to him before
the ambulance got here?

1145
01:24:39,880 --> 01:24:41,080
No, sir.

1146
01:24:41,160 --> 01:24:42,520
What did you get?

1147
01:24:42,600 --> 01:24:43,760
His address, sir.

1148
01:24:45,320 --> 01:24:46,680
Is that all?

1149
01:24:49,160 --> 01:24:50,160
Well?

1150
01:24:58,920 --> 01:25:00,920
You enter this
on your report?

1151
01:25:01,000 --> 01:25:02,520
Not yet, sir.

1152
01:25:04,520 --> 01:25:05,640
Why not?

1153
01:25:05,720 --> 01:25:07,160
I was, uh...

1154
01:25:07,240 --> 01:25:09,880
waiting for
instructions, sir.

1155
01:25:09,960 --> 01:25:11,360
You never saw it.

1156
01:25:13,320 --> 01:25:14,360
Yes, sir.

1157
01:25:17,160 --> 01:25:20,440
Oh, uh...
what's your full name?

1158
01:25:20,520 --> 01:25:23,160
Jackson Reilly, sir.
21st Precinct.

1159
01:25:23,240 --> 01:25:27,160
OK. I'll remember it.

1160
01:25:38,280 --> 01:25:41,400
Reporter: Inspector, is it true
that you have the vigilante in there?

1161
01:25:41,480 --> 01:25:42,520
Ochoa: No.

1162
01:25:42,600 --> 01:25:44,160
Well, who <i>have</i> you
got there?

1163
01:25:47,880 --> 01:25:49,240
You in charge?

1164
01:25:49,320 --> 01:25:50,680
How is he?

1165
01:25:50,760 --> 01:25:52,120
Wounds are clean.
Nothing vital.

1166
01:25:52,200 --> 01:25:53,880
We have a transfusion
going on now.

1167
01:25:53,960 --> 01:25:55,960
Soon as we get some blood in him,
we'll sew him up.

1168
01:25:56,040 --> 01:25:56,920
Is he in there?

1169
01:25:57,000 --> 01:25:57,880
Yeah.

1170
01:25:57,960 --> 01:25:59,160
All right if I go in?

1171
01:25:59,240 --> 01:26:00,760
He won't be able
to talk much.

1172
01:26:00,840 --> 01:26:02,040
Can he hear me?

1173
01:26:02,120 --> 01:26:03,160
He is conscious.

1174
01:26:05,160 --> 01:26:07,960
[Indistinct P.A. Announcement]

1175
01:26:13,320 --> 01:26:15,920
Police. I'd like to
have him alone.

1176
01:26:30,520 --> 01:26:32,360
Good evening,
Mr. Kersey.

1177
01:26:38,200 --> 01:26:40,320
This is your gun,
Mr. Kersey.

1178
01:26:41,880 --> 01:26:45,160
We tried to give you
a chance to get rid of it.

1179
01:26:45,240 --> 01:26:47,400
You wouldn't take it.

1180
01:26:47,480 --> 01:26:49,160
Do you hear me OK?

1181
01:26:50,840 --> 01:26:52,040
We, uh...

1182
01:26:52,120 --> 01:26:54,520
have here a
peculiar situation, Mr. Kersey.

1183
01:26:54,600 --> 01:26:57,480
We find it necessary
to make you a proposition,

1184
01:26:57,560 --> 01:27:01,320
since you are not
going to favor us by dying.

1185
01:27:01,400 --> 01:27:05,960
You, uh, work for a company
with lots of offices.

1186
01:27:06,040 --> 01:27:08,680
Get a transfer
to another city,

1187
01:27:08,760 --> 01:27:11,560
and I'll drop this gun
in the river.

1188
01:27:15,160 --> 01:27:19,240
Are we connecting,
Mr. Kersey?

1189
01:27:20,800 --> 01:27:24,120
We want you to get
out of New York...

1190
01:27:24,200 --> 01:27:26,080
permanently.

1191
01:27:31,120 --> 01:27:32,480
Inspector.

1192
01:27:36,200 --> 01:27:37,560
By sundown?

1193
01:27:42,040 --> 01:27:44,640
[Sneezes]

1194
01:27:53,360 --> 01:27:54,760
Reporters:
There he is. Here he comes.

1195
01:27:54,840 --> 01:27:56,440
Do you have the vigilante,
Inspector?

1196
01:27:56,520 --> 01:27:58,040
Can't you give us
some information, Inspector?

1197
01:27:58,120 --> 01:27:59,200
No!

1198
01:27:59,280 --> 01:28:00,960
Isn't the wounded man
the vigilante, Inspector?

1199
01:28:01,040 --> 01:28:02,600
No. He's just
a mugging victim.

1200
01:28:02,680 --> 01:28:05,560
How do you explain the first reports
that he <i>is</i> the vigilante?

1201
01:28:05,640 --> 01:28:07,720
False reports.
It happens all the time.

1202
01:28:07,800 --> 01:28:09,360
Then the vigilante's
still out there?

1203
01:28:09,440 --> 01:28:11,920
That's right. He's still
out there on the streets.

1204
01:28:12,000 --> 01:28:12,960
Let me through.

1205
01:28:13,040 --> 01:28:16,000
Was he shot
by the vigilante, then?

1206
01:28:25,880 --> 01:28:28,680
P.A.: The Amtrak train
from New York to Chicago

1207
01:28:28,760 --> 01:28:30,320
has arrived on track 8.

1208
01:28:30,400 --> 01:28:31,440
Man: Mr. Kersey.

1209
01:28:31,520 --> 01:28:32,560
Paul Kersey.

1210
01:28:32,640 --> 01:28:34,320
Fred Brown.
Welcome to Chicago, sir.

1211
01:28:34,400 --> 01:28:35,760
Did you have a nice trip?

1212
01:28:35,840 --> 01:28:36,880
Yeah, it was OK.

1213
01:28:36,960 --> 01:28:38,960
Good. I found a nice
apartment for you.

1214
01:28:39,040 --> 01:28:40,400
I hope you like it.
It's on Lake Shore Drive.

1215
01:28:40,480 --> 01:28:41,960
You have a view
of Lake Michigan, morning sun.

1216
01:28:42,040 --> 01:28:43,920
We've got your office
ready, too.

1217
01:28:44,000 --> 01:28:46,640
There's a very good
golf club, if you play.

1218
01:28:46,720 --> 01:28:48,720
Listen, I think
you'll enjoy it here.

1219
01:28:48,800 --> 01:28:50,480
Excuse me.

